            <h2>My Journey into Robotics</h2>
            <p>
               Whenever I see someone say they’ve been coding since they were 11, it totally intimidates me, and I immediately put them on a pedestal. But I had this pretty cool realization that shifted my perspective. I’ve always had a crush on robotics & intelligent systems since I was 7 I just never had a creative outlet for that drive or the resources. I got into robotics, Arduino, and hardware programming when I was around 14-15. Before that, at 12, I was making makeshift projects with random junk at home—like lighters and other weird stuff. It was interesting, to say the least, but nothing really came of it.

Still, that drive from those early days gives me the strength to pursue really cool projects and papers I’m working on now at Kozot with my founding partner and close friend. Looking back, some of those first projects were pretty cringy, but they’ve got a special place in my heart. I’ve got a couple of videos showcasing those early attempts which is just soooo adorable. I even got as far as making remote-controlled cars with servo arms, though I can’t seem to find any presentations or videos of those projects. I'll upload a picture or a video later showcasing the project dont expect me to present like back then tho lol &#128539;
            </p>
